AttributeList.Text: This block contains the logic and futher calls (e.g. sequences, control modules, diagnostics etc.) of the equipment module.

This block links and unlinks the EM from the unit. The command to link/unlink can be set directly by the inputs of the block (e.g. to link/unlink based on any program logic) or through the InOut "hmiInterface". The block changes the output "isLinked" to true/false, depending on the command and if a change is allowed. A changed is allowed if the unit is in state aborted, clearing or stopped. The output "isLinked" is send back to the unit. If the EM is not linked, the unit ignores this EM.

When linked, unitStatus is fully applied to unitStatusUsed. When not linked, only acknowledge and safetyReleased from the unitStatus are applied. A direct EM control by hmiInterface or localInterface is possible.

This block maps the unit status to the seuqnce status. Thus, it controls the sequence depending on the unit status. E.g. it sets the sequence to automatic when the unit state is in productions. This blocks work perfectly with the sequences provided in the AF. This typed block (MapUnitStatusToSequence) could be adjusted to specific application requirements or if other, user-defined sequences are used.
Map Unit Status to Sequence Status
Configure here when the jobs of the sequence should be started. More jobs could be added. This is optional and work perfectly when you use an AF sequence.
Set em to initialized here. Usually this is done when the initialization job is completed.
Call of the em logic. Here you can add an AF sequence (provided as master copies in the library in three versiones: programmend in LAD, GRAPH or SCL). You can also use your own sequence block.
Call control modules that are actuators after the em logic (jobs and sequence), so that the latest commands are applied to the actuators.
Conditions for the Equipment Modules "stateComplete" feedback to the unit. This feedback is given when the task in for the respective state is complete.
Conditions for the Equipment Modules "stateComplete" feedback to the unit. This feedback is given when the task in for the respective state is complete.
Add events here that trigger alarms and lead to the respective commands to the unit. It is possible to trigger alarms, set unit commands or do both for the specific event

Derive commands from the ProDiag supervision. The ProDiag supervisions contain categories which define the reaction of these supervisions (e.g. abort, stop, hold). These are handed over as commands to the unit level. Alternatively, if no ProDiag should be used, you can use the LAF_ManageBitAlarms to realize bit alarm handling. This block can be found in LAF in folder 70_AlarmHandling.
